{"data":{"biocliVersion":"0.5.0","data":{"symbol":"KRAS","name":"KRAS proto-oncogene, GTPase","summary":"This gene, a Kirsten ras oncogene homolog from the mammalian ras gene family, encodes a protein that is a member of the small GTPase superfamily. A single amino acid substitution is responsible for an activating mutation. The transforming protein that results is implicated in various malignancies...","chromosome":"12","location":"12p12.1","function":"Ras proteins bind GDP/GTP and possess intrinsic GTPase activity (PubMed:20949621, PubMed:39809765). Plays an important role in the regulation of cell proliferation (PubMed:22711838, PubMed:23698361). Activates MAPK1/MAPK3 resulting in phosphorylation and ultimately degradation of GJA1 (By similarity). Plays a role in promoting oncogenic events by inducing transcriptional silencing of tumor suppressor genes (TSGs) in colorectal cancer (CRC) cells in a ZNF304-dependent manner (PubMed:24623306)","subcellularLocation":"Cell membrane, Endomembrane system, Cytoplasm, cytosol","pathways":[{"id":"hsa01521","name":"EGFR tyrosine kinase inhibitor resistance","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa01522","name":"Endocrine resistance","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04010","name":"MAPK signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04012","name":"ErbB signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04014","name":"Ras signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04015","name":"Rap1 signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04062","name":"Chemokine signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04068","name":"FoxO signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04071","name":"Sphingolipid signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04072","name":"Phospholipase D signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04137","name":"Mitophagy","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04140","name":"Autophagy","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04150","name":"mTOR signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa04151","name":"PI3K-Akt signaling pathway","source":"KEGG"},{"id":"hsa0